name: protoporphyrinogen oxidase
classes: Acting on the CH-CH group of donors;
reaction: protoporphyrinogen IX + 3 O2 = protoporphyrin IX + 3 H2O2 [RN:R03222]
comment: This is the last common enzyme in the biosynthesis of chlorophylls and heme [8]. Two isoenzymes exist in plants: one in plastids and the other in mitochondria. This is the target enzyme of phthalimide-type and diphenylether-type herbicides [8]. The enzyme from oxygen-dependent species contains FAD [9]. Also slowly oxidizes mesoporphyrinogen IX.
